@startuml pipelineuml
actor Developer
participant "GitHub" as GH
participant "CI/CD Pipeline" as CI
participant "Self-Hosted Runner" as Runner
participant "Test Environment" as TestEnv
participant "Production" as Prod

Developer -> GH: Push to Feature Branch (SSH)
Developer -> GH: Create Pull Request to main (HTTPS)
GH -> CI: Trigger Linting & Tests (Webhook)
CI -> Runner: Deploy Test Environment (GitHub Action, Self-Hosted Runner)
Runner -> TestEnv: Deploy & Run Tests ()
TestEnv -> Runner: Report Test Results (HTTP API)

alt Tests Successful
    Developer -> GH: Merge PR to main (HTTPS)
    GH -> CI: Trigger Build Pipeline (Webhook)
    CI -> Runner: Build & Release Images (GitHub Action, Docker Registry, HTTPS)
    Runner -> GH: Increase Semantic Version (GitHub Action)
    Runner -> GH: Publish Release (GitHub Repository)
else Tests Fail
    CI -> Developer: Notify about failed tests (Email, Slack API)
end

@enduml